3
00:00:12,280 --> 00:00:18,634
Sahasrara Puja,

4
00:00:18,714 --> 00:00:24,180
in the chapel of the castle of Mesnières, Rouen (France), 6 May 1984. Shri Mataji:

5
00:00:24,260 --> 00:00:29,661
All right, be seated.

6
00:00:29,741 --> 00:00:31,074
All of you are here?

7
00:00:37,681 --> 00:00:39,814
Ask them to get some tea for Me.

8
00:00:39,894 --> 00:00:43,160
Tea or coffee, it will be all right.First of all,

9
00:00:43,240 --> 00:00:51,139
we have to thank the French Sahaja Yogis who have arranged this program for us.

10
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:40,540
So, give them a hand.[Applause]We have to thank all the leaders

11
00:02:06,481 --> 00:02:11,901
from all Sahaja Yoga centres in Europe and in England who have

12
00:02:11,981 --> 00:02:18,693
helped to arrange this

13
00:02:18,773 --> 00:02:25,486
program.[Applause]You

14
00:02:25,566 --> 00:02:30,940
are the leaders;

15
00:02:31,020 --> 00:02:36,930
you are clapping to yourselves!

16
00:02:37,010 --> 00:02:43,821
[Laughter]So, last of all but

17
00:02:43,901 --> 00:02:48,521
not least of all, we have to thank, I thank,

18
00:02:48,601 --> 00:02:54,786
all the Sahaja Yogis

19
00:02:54,866 --> 00:02:59,496
for coming all

20
00:02:59,576 --> 00:03:11,096
the way to this castle.[Applause]So,

21
00:03:11,176 --> 00:03:17,621
as a token of my gratitude, for all of you,

22
00:03:17,701 --> 00:03:21,001
I would like to give some

23
00:03:21,081 --> 00:03:27,180
little presents to the different centres of your opening land.

24
00:03:28,040 --> 00:03:35,160
So, as we call the names of people, one by one, we should come, now Gavin,

25
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:42,320
because the handwriting is written by people that you cannot read.

26
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:47,586
First the centres, you take on.

27
00:03:50,788 --> 00:03:53,588
Move it the other way round. It’s correct,

28
00:03:53,668 --> 00:04:00,060
it comes out correctly. Now, let’s start.Now we have done one thing.

29
00:04:00,660 --> 00:04:05,220
First of all, all the leaders of the centres will be called,

30
00:04:05,300 --> 00:04:09,366
of the countries, will be called and given a present to them.

31
00:04:10,420 --> 00:04:17,231
And, after that, we’ll be calling some of the leaders

32
00:04:17,311 --> 00:04:20,820
whom we have not yet given

33
00:04:20,900 --> 00:04:27,440
presents, but I would like some of the senior leaders to give them the presents.

34
00:04:27,520 --> 00:04:31,461
So, it will be a generosity on their parts.

35
00:04:31,541 --> 00:04:35,620
Because I have put those names which are the leaders already.

36
00:04:37,140 --> 00:04:42,073
And I think it will be very generous on their part to give these presents.

37
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:05,920
Then this is to be cut into pieces.

38
00:05:36,340 --> 00:05:39,020
Has anybody got pair of scissors?

39
00:05:39,100 --> 00:05:43,300
Sahaja Yogi: Yes.Shri Mataji: That’s good.

40
00:06:01,580 --> 00:06:08,480
Now take them in, one by one.

41
01:17:07,188 --> 01:17:12,321
Now, if you have any questions, I would like to answer them and then I’ll you

42
01:17:12,401 --> 01:17:15,740
something about Sahaja Yoga.[Aside] Gavin,

43
01:17:15,820 --> 01:17:18,620
can you keep these letters it’s important.

44
01:17:27,120 --> 01:17:30,740
This is a funny thing Nick is telling to his wife.

45
01:17:31,207 --> 01:17:35,140
He doesn’t want her to speak Marathi and wants [inaudible].

46
01:17:35,220 --> 01:17:40,900
He doesn’t allow her to speak to any Sahaja Yogis.

47
01:18:07,960 --> 01:18:15,670
What’s the time?Sahaja Yogi: Nine twenty pm.Shri Mataji: All right. So,

48
01:18:15,750 --> 01:18:21,560
just ask Me questions.Gregoire:

49
01:18:57,280 --> 01:19:02,701
How can we better protect ourselves if we work in an

50
01:19:02,781 --> 01:19:05,960
environment which is against Sahaj?Shri Mataji:

51
01:19:06,040 --> 01:19:08,506
That’s the place you have to work it.

52
01:19:29,840 --> 01:19:33,400
I will tell you later on, on this point, more.

53
01:19:37,440 --> 01:19:39,606
Later,

54
01:19:39,686 --> 01:19:45,530
on the lecture,

55
01:19:45,610 --> 01:19:51,740
I’ll tell you on this point.

56
01:19:51,820 --> 01:19:57,096
Now another question. Gregoire:

57
01:19:57,176 --> 01:20:02,099
Is there a particular advice

58
01:20:02,179 --> 01:20:06,120
to keep the Sahasrara

59
01:20:06,200 --> 01:20:09,020
open and clear?Shri Mataji:

60
01:20:09,100 --> 01:20:15,320
All right, I’ll answer this also.

61
01:20:26,180 --> 01:20:28,246
I can answer this question now.

62
01:20:29,288 --> 01:20:31,421
It’s very simple, as I told you,

63
01:20:31,501 --> 01:20:37,981
that the deity of Sahasrara is sitting before you, that the deity

64
01:20:38,061 --> 01:20:40,120
of Sahasrara is Mahamaya,

65
01:20:41,520 --> 01:20:47,700
that try not to understand Her through your reasoning and imagination.

66
01:20:48,360 --> 01:20:54,700
But by surrendering absolutely to it, you keep your Sahasrara open.

67
01:20:56,500 --> 01:21:02,240
In case you still find- [to Gregoire] just one sentence more- it is still closed,

68
01:21:02,320 --> 01:21:06,301
you have to ask for forgiveness from the deity that,

69
01:21:06,381 --> 01:21:13,053
“If we have by mistake made any mistakes, so please forgive us”. That’s all.

70
01:21:57,080 --> 01:22:03,705
All right, now,

71
01:22:03,785 --> 01:22:11,489
what is the other

72
01:22:11,569 --> 01:22:20,186
question?Gregoire:

73
01:22:20,266 --> 01:22:23,881
There is

74
01:22:23,961 --> 01:22:31,081
a specific question.

75
01:22:31,161 --> 01:22:36,161
It is advised that children should sleep in the same room as their parents.

76
01:22:36,241 --> 01:22:39,574
But if they wake up four, five times in the night,

77
01:22:39,654 --> 01:22:44,054
is it possible to put them in a separate room?Shri Mataji: No, no.

78
01:22:44,134 --> 01:22:47,000
Then the mother should sleep with the child

79
01:22:47,080 --> 01:22:50,080
and the father should sleep in another room.

80
01:22:50,160 --> 01:22:52,560
Mother should never leave the child.

81
01:22:55,800 --> 01:22:59,587
Moreover, I would advise you that now you have children,

82
01:22:59,667 --> 01:23:02,800
don’t get too much involved with your children.

83
01:23:02,880 --> 01:23:04,546
That’s a dangerous thing.

84
01:23:04,626 --> 01:23:09,946
This is another phase: first, they get involved with the wives or husbands,

85
01:23:10,026 --> 01:23:12,966
then they get involved with the children.

86
01:23:13,046 --> 01:23:18,960
If you get involved with the children, then again, you have to restart many things.

87
01:23:19,040 --> 01:23:20,620
So, don’t get involved.

88
01:23:21,260 --> 01:23:26,775
You have to just do the work like a trustee of the child,

89
01:23:26,855 --> 01:23:29,061
just a trustee of the child.

90
01:23:29,141 --> 01:23:32,821
But don’t get involved with the child. That is my job.

91
01:23:33,341 --> 01:23:35,141
You have to leave it to Me.

92
01:23:35,221 --> 01:23:38,554
So, don’t get too much involved with the children.

93
01:23:38,634 --> 01:23:44,274
I find people who got children, you see, are going now wrtiting literature on it.

94
01:23:44,354 --> 01:23:45,620
Don’t do like that.

95
01:23:46,228 --> 01:23:50,694
I’ve already given instructions what is to be done about the child.

96
01:23:50,774 --> 01:23:53,240
But the children are mine, not yours.

97
01:23:53,320 --> 01:23:58,520
So, you just don’t get involved into them because that’s a temptation for you.

98
01:23:58,600 --> 01:24:02,866
Too much involvement in the children is the sign of degradation.

99
01:24:04,107 --> 01:24:07,853
It’s only a responsibility to look after it. That’s all.

100
01:24:09,900 --> 01:24:16,439
So, tell them.And mother must be with children, must be with children.

101
01:25:08,420 --> 01:25:10,220
She should sleep with them;

102
01:25:10,300 --> 01:25:14,233
she should look after them till they are five years of age.

103
01:25:18,680 --> 01:25:23,827
If she has to go out, then she must know that she has to carry the child.

104
01:25:23,907 --> 01:25:27,160
She cannot leave children. That’s not good.

105
01:25:27,240 --> 01:25:32,773
She should never leave the child before they are five years of age, whatever it is.

106
01:25:43,714 --> 01:25:46,580
Because you should know that till that age,

107
01:25:46,660 --> 01:25:50,180
five years of age, the child is growing very fast.

108
01:25:50,675 --> 01:25:54,941
You see, at an old age, say, somebody is ninety and ninety-five,

109
01:25:55,021 --> 01:25:56,954
there is not much difference.

110
01:26:08,280 --> 01:26:12,220
And at that time, the sense of security must be maintained.

111
01:26:12,320 --> 01:26:13,653
That, one has to do!

112
01:26:20,360 --> 01:26:25,707
So, if the husband has to do something else or if he has to go out or anything,

113
01:26:25,787 --> 01:26:27,720
he can go with other friends,

114
01:26:27,800 --> 01:26:34,040
the boys, or other Sahaja Yogis, but the mother must look after the children,

115
01:26:34,140 --> 01:26:36,406
that’s her duty, she has to do it!

116
01:26:41,680 --> 01:26:46,460
And of course, the husband must help her, must do whatever is needed.

117
01:26:46,540 --> 01:26:52,755
But here the question is of shifting the similarity.

118
01:26:52,835 --> 01:26:55,701
Now, at this time, the mother is important.

119
01:26:55,781 --> 01:26:59,381
She has to look after the child, that’s her first job.

120
01:26:59,461 --> 01:27:04,000
And at time, the husband’s job becomes a secondary thing.

121
01:27:05,140 --> 01:27:06,941
But hers is the first job.

122
01:27:07,021 --> 01:27:14,680
And later on, then, it again shifts because husband’s work becomes more important.

123
01:27:26,180 --> 01:27:31,447
If you give them now the security complete, the children,

124
01:27:31,527 --> 01:27:35,660
you’ll find, will be very peaceful and that’s what Indians do.

125
01:27:35,740 --> 01:27:37,940
You have seen how Indians behave.

126
01:27:38,760 --> 01:27:41,380
They are so quiet, so peaceful.

127
01:27:41,460 --> 01:27:46,400
Because completely the mothers forget about the whole world.

128
01:27:46,500 --> 01:27:51,240
You’ll be surprised, till my younger daughter was five years of age,

129
01:27:51,320 --> 01:27:53,920
I never have, went out with my husband.

130
01:28:17,340 --> 01:28:22,321
And women should not unduly feel that to look after the child

131
01:28:22,401 --> 01:28:26,420
is a lower job and to work in the office is a higher job.

132
01:28:43,980 --> 01:28:48,580
Because that pays more money or gives you artificial powers.

133
01:28:52,520 --> 01:28:57,120
You must know the greatest power in this world is that of the mother.

134
01:29:00,108 --> 01:29:05,441
And unless and until you give that much to your child, the child is not going to

135
01:29:05,521 --> 01:29:13,010
give you back that discipline, that respect,

136
01:29:13,090 --> 01:29:19,320
that glory, that you expect as parents.

137
01:29:34,180 --> 01:29:39,380
There should be a rapport between the child and the parents and understanding.

138
01:29:39,460 --> 01:29:43,920
They should talk and not give toys all the time but talk to them,

139
01:29:44,000 --> 01:29:46,933
even when they don’t talk, you talk to them.

140
01:29:51,620 --> 01:30:01,570
And that will improve cases.All

141
01:30:01,650 --> 01:30:10,903
right, so what is the

142
01:30:10,983 --> 01:30:15,720
second one?

143
01:30:19,360 --> 01:30:26,250
Gregoire: Can you talk about discrimination,

144
01:30:26,330 --> 01:30:30,040
Shri Mataji?Shri Mataji:

145
01:30:34,880 --> 01:30:38,080
It’s an innate quality, you can’t talk about it.

146
01:30:38,860 --> 01:30:44,621
Discrimination is not rational.It’s an innate quality but the best thing you

147
01:30:44,701 --> 01:30:50,501
have are vibrations by which you should see if the things are all right or not.

148
01:30:50,581 --> 01:30:54,468
But you must know as Sahaja Yogis, as you’ll grow,

149
01:30:54,548 --> 01:30:58,214
you will know immediately what is good and what is bad.

150
01:30:58,294 --> 01:31:01,427
It’s a state in which you just become discreet.

151
01:31:01,507 --> 01:31:06,240
But for that [what] you must know is to have your responses controlled,

152
01:31:06,320 --> 01:31:08,888
a steady response to anything.

153
01:31:08,968 --> 01:31:13,901
And you just, for example, you see something, for a minute you just become

154
01:31:13,981 --> 01:31:19,734
into thoughtless awareness and you’ll have the power of discretion.

155
01:31:19,814 --> 01:31:25,026
It’s a power, it is not a thing that can be discussed or taught. It’s a power.

156
01:31:52,360 --> 01:31:56,681
So, one has to develop that state and the best way is to,

157
01:31:56,761 --> 01:31:58,741
at any confrontation, anything

158
01:31:58,821 --> 01:32:00,421
that you face, first,

159
01:32:00,501 --> 01:32:05,034
you become thoughtlessly aware so you enter into the kingdom of God.

160
01:32:17,700 --> 01:32:19,120
And then react.

161
01:32:22,960 --> 01:32:28,494
The responses must

162
01:32:28,574 --> 01:32:32,560
be made very

163
01:32:32,640 --> 01:32:36,107
steady and subtle.And one should

164
01:32:36,187 --> 01:32:40,120
not suddenly change the attentions, you see, “Just now, now

165
01:32:40,200 --> 01:32:45,530
everybody’s attention, their mind is not”.

166
01:32:45,610 --> 01:32:49,361
[A loudspeaker has been

167
01:32:49,441 --> 01:32:55,160
moved.]I did the job.Gregoire: Once again.Shri Mataji: All right?

168
01:32:55,700 --> 01:32:57,880
The attention now is with Me.

169
01:32:57,960 --> 01:33:03,293
Suddenly, all of you turn [your head], what is there to see? Who is responsible?

170
01:33:20,747 --> 01:33:24,480
So, those who put their attention there, pull your ears.

171
01:33:24,560 --> 01:33:31,062
[Shri Mataji laughs]

172
01:33:31,142 --> 01:33:36,990
I think everybody

173
01:33:37,070 --> 01:33:47,400
should do it.All right, so.

174
01:33:47,480 --> 01:33:50,500
Now, what’s the other question?

175
01:33:54,920 --> 01:33:56,120
Yes, yes.

176
01:34:00,460 --> 01:34:07,600
Gregoire: For an artist who is a Sahaja Yogi,

177
01:34:07,680 --> 01:34:10,081
what means to create

178
01:34:10,161 --> 01:34:17,474
a piece of art?Shri Mataji: The piece of art must emit vibrations.

179
01:34:19,394 --> 01:34:22,994
It does not emit: that means there is something wrong.

180
01:34:28,574 --> 01:34:31,587
And going for something, higher subjects,

181
01:34:31,667 --> 01:34:34,947
like Kundalini, like the expression of Kundalini,

182
01:34:35,027 --> 01:34:40,560
the colours of Kundalini, and into another world, you have to move into that world.

183
01:34:40,640 --> 01:34:43,440
Like, you can see we have so many artists.

184
01:34:43,520 --> 01:34:46,280
For example, you can say Blake.

185
01:35:00,300 --> 01:35:05,181
And for a Sahaja Yogi, it should be a kind of a beautiful integration

186
01:35:05,261 --> 01:35:11,767
of the gross and the abstract or realistic and abstract you can say.

187
01:35:30,027 --> 01:35:32,387
And a little bit of impressionism.

188
01:35:36,488 --> 01:35:39,888
That’s how you should try to integrate all of them.

189
01:35:39,968 --> 01:35:41,547
They express one style;

190
01:35:41,627 --> 01:35:46,693
a Sahaja Yogi has no style because he knows how to mix up, how to integrate.

191
01:35:57,967 --> 01:36:01,233
But certain colours like black should be avoided.

192
01:36:04,087 --> 01:36:07,687
But the pastels colours, if they are mixed with black,

193
01:36:07,767 --> 01:36:11,300
it gives a depth to the pastel colours. [To Gregoire]

194
01:36:11,380 --> 01:36:15,281
Pastel.[Laughter

195
01:36:15,361 --> 01:36:19,510
because Gregoire

196
01:36:19,590 --> 01:36:25,661
cannot translate]Now,

197
01:36:25,741 --> 01:36:28,741
your Mother’s attention goes to Sahaja Yogis.

198
01:36:28,821 --> 01:36:30,860
That’s my attention is.

199
01:36:38,480 --> 01:36:43,541
And it is such a remarkable attention that it is describing, “kataksha,

200
01:36:43,621 --> 01:36:51,020
kataksha, nirikshan [inspection]” means, “every glance examines and acts”.

201
01:37:03,240 --> 01:37:09,679
So, when you have that attention, then it’s all right to see everything,

202
01:37:09,759 --> 01:37:12,292
because it is so deep and penetrating.

203
01:37:40,720 --> 01:37:45,120
Shri Mataji: Yes.Gregoire: For the people for a reason or another,

204
01:37:45,200 --> 01:37:47,000
they cannot live in ashram.

205
01:37:47,080 --> 01:37:52,480
So, how would such people know that they are growing in collectivity?Shri Mataji:

206
01:37:56,420 --> 01:38:01,220
Growth in collectivity creates joy, fun, happiness.

207
01:38:01,920 --> 01:38:09,297
No discussion, no argument

208
01:38:09,377 --> 01:38:19,724
comes in, especially with

209
01:38:19,804 --> 01:38:24,320
the leader,

210
01:38:24,400 --> 01:38:27,840
and what are your relations, that’s very important.

211
01:38:40,720 --> 01:38:42,920
Now if you fight with the leader,

212
01:38:43,000 --> 01:38:47,930
then something ‘s wrong with you.You have

213
01:38:48,010 --> 01:38:54,160
no right to fight with the leader.

214
01:39:00,340 --> 01:39:03,880
Now if the leader becomes absolutely unpopular,

215
01:39:03,960 --> 01:39:06,693
then he is no more a leader, that I know.

216
01:39:18,220 --> 01:39:21,500
But he has to be unpopular in the whole world.

217
01:39:35,834 --> 01:39:38,900
[Laughter]Say, for example, if there is mister

218
01:39:38,980 --> 01:39:42,321
X who is popular in the country – who is a

219
01:39:42,401 --> 01:39:45,500
leader and who is unpopular in a country Y.

220
01:39:51,200 --> 01:39:54,800
Now that is no judgment because they might be jealous.

221
01:39:57,840 --> 01:40:04,440
They think they are equal to him and can fight him back and can shut him down.

222
01:40:10,880 --> 01:40:16,180
And no administration can work like that,

223
01:40:16,260 --> 01:40:21,220
least of all, Divine administration.

224
01:40:30,420 --> 01:40:34,486
So, those who fight the leader are first of all uncollective.

225
01:40:41,180 --> 01:40:45,990
Actually, India is the best way to find out,

226
01:40:46,070 --> 01:40:52,340
they come and tell Me about who is who.

227
01:41:02,120 --> 01:41:07,453
So, I would put it like this, very grossly that you have to be popular in India.

228
01:41:23,140 --> 01:41:29,934
And the Indian’s leaders have to be popular otherwise, in other countries.

229
01:41:38,994 --> 01:41:43,394
But perhaps I have some sense of discretion and I know who is who.

230
01:41:54,574 --> 01:41:59,654
[Laughter]So, somebody who is a leader, you should not fight, first of all.

231
01:42:12,074 --> 01:42:15,874
You should not- if he is strict, if he is harsh with you,

232
01:42:15,954 --> 01:42:19,754
take it with a grace and be happy that you are corrected.

233
01:42:27,014 --> 01:42:30,894
But if you give an explanation or if you fight it back or

234
01:42:30,974 --> 01:42:35,040
you think that you are all right, then you can never improve.

235
01:42:48,028 --> 01:42:48,694
I’ve seen,

236
01:42:48,774 --> 01:42:54,040
there are some Sahaja Yogis and Sahaja Yoginis who have been with us for years,

237
01:42:54,120 --> 01:42:57,186
and they have not improved at all because they

238
01:42:57,266 --> 01:43:00,199
think that there is nothing wrong with them.

239
01:43:09,987 --> 01:43:13,720
Sometimes I shout at them because the bhoots have to go.

240
01:43:13,800 --> 01:43:17,800
So, they say, “All right, Mother has shouted at our bhoots”.

241
01:43:29,940 --> 01:43:32,740
And they never want to look at themselves.

